Rapper Flo Milli Musical Escapades: A New Album and Single on the Horizon

The hip-hop scene is about to get a fresh wave of Flo Milli magic. The Alabama-born rapper has just dropped a bombshell – a new album is brewing. Titled Fine Ho, Stay, the album’s release date remains under wraps. However, a press release teases that it’s set to hit the airwaves later this summer.

Find a guide to Flo Milli, with all her best songs.

To whet the appetite of her fans, Flo Milli has released the album’s first single, “Fruit Loop.” The track, a vibrant showcase of her lyrical prowess, comes with a music video directed by the talented Chandler Lass. Scroll down to experience the “Fruit Loop” phenomenon. Listen below:

A Glimpse into Flo Milli’s Musical Journey

Fine Ho, Stay is the second studio album from Flo Milli, a follow-up to her previous album, You Still Here, Ho ?, which graced the hip-hop scene last year. Before these albums, Flo Milli made her mark with the breakout mixtape Ho, why is you here ? in 2020.

Flo Milli’s journey in the music industry has been nothing short of impressive. She has shown versatility by reworking Lil Wayne’s iconic “A Milli” into a track named after herself. Watch below:

The Fabulous Flo Milli: A Brief Bio

Born Tamia Monique Carter, but known to the world as Flo Milli, this hip-hop sensation hails from Mobile, Alabama. She arrived on the scene on January 9, 2000, and has been making waves ever since.

As a young girl, Flo Milli was already flexing her creative muscles. She began penning songs in elementary school when most of us struggled with multiplication tables. By age 11, she was not just rapping but had formed a rap group called Real & Beautiful. The group later underwent a name change, emerging as the Pink Mafia. Talk about starting young and aiming high!

Flo Milli’s big break came when her tracks “Beef FloMix” and “In the Party” took TikTok by storm. These viral hits didn’t just earn her millions of views and gold certification from the Recording Industry Association of America.
